ne+Sheet+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%283%2F3%2F25%29&utm_content=3DLine+Sheet+-+SUBSCRIB=
ERS+%283%2F3%2F25%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm=
_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a )

=E2=80=8A

You could say Simone Bellotti came into Bally like a lamb and went out like=
 a lion. His
first show, just a year and a half ago, was a modest proposal, but the cowb=
ells ringing on the bags and dangling off his now-famous moccasins showed t=
hat the designer wasn=E2=80=99t afraid to make a little noise. For his four=
th season, Bellotti had a soundtrack designed for the runway by Berlin DJ a=
nd producer PLO Man, and =E2=80=9Ccurated by Threes.=E2=80=9D I=E2=80=99m n=
ot going to act like I know what any of those words mean, but the noise was=
 assertive, just like the collection.

Fall/Winter
2025 was a progression of Bellotti=E2=80=99s previous silhouettes and ideas=
=E2=80=94the lewd use of fur, the nipped-in waist for both men and women=E2=
=80=94but with more aggressive use of black and leather. The venue=E2=80=94=
the architecturally significant Velasca Tower, a midcentury, mushroom-shape=
d marvel designed ( https://www.atlasobscura.com/places/torre-velasca?utm_c=
ampaign=3DLine+Sheet+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%283%2F3%2F25%29&utm_content=3DLine+Shee=
t+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%283%2F3%2F25%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcus=
tomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) by BBPR=E2=80=94was a progression,=
 too, less deferential to Bally=E2=80=99s Swiss heritage and more
obviously aligned with Bellotti=E2=80=99s personal taste. From the outside,=
 Velasca was designed to look fairly traditional, except not. (I want to di=
e on this building=E2=80=99s linoleum floors, which is possible since it is=
 mixed use, with both offices and apartments.)=C2=A0

