mer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) on the Bally.com homepage), as well =
as the inevitable uptick in sales pegged to Bellotti=E2=80=99s moccasins, e=
t al., perhaps Regent has intentions of making a real go of it.

I hope they do. It=E2=80=99s a shame that former Bally
owner JAB Holding=E2=80=94which was desperate to get out of the fashion gam=
e after its failed attempt at forming a strategic group=E2=80=94gave up whe=
n they did. My understanding is that some people associated with the Reiman=
n family investment vehicle urged them to hold on once Bellotti was install=
ed and showed promise, but they were already resigned at that point. Anyway=
, no sense in playing what-ifs. OTB=E2=80=99s Renzo Rosso and newly appoint=
ed Jil Sander C.E.O. (and LVMH alum)
Serge Brunschwig just hired one of the few designers working right now who =
can move product. Lucky them, and lucky him.

